<br>
SOE plays some sort of a cruel joke making the first (oh yes, the first) step in a cleric’s epic quest take forever.  I’m told that Begurgle can possibly take over 10hours straight of camping his placeholder before he spawns.  This is so friggin dumb.  I can understand making the last parts of the epic very difficult (long spawn times, super hard mobs, etc.) but why in the world must the first step be like that??  Maybe some people’s idea of fun is being at the bottom of a murky lake staring at the same thing for hours on end.  Next time I’m gonna load up on ale and drink my sorrows away while I’m cold and wet waiting for Begurgle come out to play.  Wish me luck lol.<br>
<br>
Thanks Chev and Nyaare for keeping me company *waves*.<br>
<br>
